title: Atelier Brancusi
description: Museum housing works by Romanian sculptor Constantin Brancusi, who lived in Paris from 1904 until his death in 1957. Many sculptures are fitted into a fairly small space, like an artist's atelier (workshop). In fact, Brancusi bequeathed his sculptures to the French state on the condition that they be displayed in a re-creation of his workshop as it was on the day he died!
